'''Domenico Serra''' (1899–1965) was an Italian [[stage actor|stage]] and [[film actor]]. He made more than sixty films, many of them during the [[silent era]] including [[Mario Bonnard]]'s historical film ''[[The Betrothed (1923 film)|The Betrothed]]'' (1923).<ref>Goble p.305</ref> In the [[sound era]], he largely played supporting or minor roles.

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[Wanda Warenine]]'' (1917)
* ''[[The Cavalcade of Dreams ]]'' (1917)
* ''[[The Shadow (1920 film)|The Shadow]]'' (1920)
* ''[[The Betrothed (1923 film)|The Betrothed]]'' (1923)
* ''[[Chief Saetta]]'' (1924)
* ''[[Pleasure Train (film)|Pleasure Train]]'' (1924)
* ''[[Steel (1933 film)|Steel]]'' (1933)
* ''[[Lost in the Dark (1947 film)|Lost in the Dark]]'' (1947)
* ''[[The Opium Den]]'' (1947)
* ''[[The Beggar's Daughter]]'' (1950) 
* ''[[Jolanda, the Daughter of the Black Corsair]]'' (1952)
* ''[[Orphan of the Ghetto]]'' (1954)
* ''[[The Song of the Heart (film)|The Song of the Heart]]'' (1955)

